PSCU President Uhuru Kenyatta yesterday held talks with Ethiopian President Sahle-Work Zewde who paid him a courtesy call at State House, Nairobi. Their discussion focused on bolstering the historical bilateral ties between Kenya and Ethiopia. President Zewde, who is in the country on a one-day official visit, was received by President Uhuru and First Lady Margaret Kenyatta at State HouseÂ  shortly after 1pm. She was accompanied by Ethiopian Ambassador to Kenya Meles Alem Tekea. The two leaders discussed a wide range of matters including mutual interest of the two nations key among them the ongoing engagements aimed at deepening diplomatic and bilateral ties between the neighbouring countries.